question: The "Pico Duarte" peak is located in which country?
explanation: Pico Duarte, which is 3098 metres above sea level, is the highest peak of the Dominican Republic in the West Indies region on the Hispaniola Islands of the Greater Antilles Archipelago. The Cordillera Central forms the parent range of this peak. This peak houses Lake Enriquillo. It is North America's ninth isolated peak.
